content:
Paruresis:
Paruresis is considered to be a social phobia. In general, if you live with paruresis, you fear negative evaluation by others related to using public toilets. If this fear is severe and limits your life, it may be diagnosed as social anxiety disorder

content:
@SENwarriormum “She’s just a very shy little girl”
“No cause for concern”
“If she was autistic she wouldn’t be able to hold it in all day and let it out at home”
Since been diagnosed with autism and ADHD and been acknowledged that she’s selective mute and has social and separation anxiety.
